&lt;h1 id="american-culture"&gt;American Culture&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nov 29 2005&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A caucasian and U.S. born friend once opined that I was lucky to have been born in a great culture (India), and that Americans have no culture. Not so. She has been living in it for so long that she is a fish in the American cultural ocean – it&amp;rsquo;s invisible. People leave the world in droves to come to America, for the culture. The culture of freedom, individual liberty, open-ness, and protection from the greatest slaughterer of mankind, government. I&amp;rsquo;ll take that any day over colorful clothing and spicy food.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>You Weren't Meant to Have a Boss</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/boss/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/boss/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/boss/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
